  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Idiopathic purpura fulminans by anti-protein S antibody is a very rare but potentially&#xD;
      extremely serious entity. The data in the literature are poor with only isolated report boxes&#xD;
      and a single series of less than 10 boxes. The creation of a larger series of cases would&#xD;
      make it possible to better understand this pathology and to offer assistance in diagnosis and&#xD;
      management.&#xD;
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
